---
const install = `brew tap mattrbdr/tap
brew install etg`;
const example = `# env.production.to.github
DATABASE_URL="postgres://..."
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...`;
const run = `gh auth login
etg info
etg --dry-run
etg`;
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="description" content="Sync GitHub environment secrets from a local env file." />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#fcfcfb" />
    <title>etg — env to GitHub</title>
    <style>
      :root { background: #fcfcfb; color: #202124; font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; } html { scroll-behavior: smooth; } body { margin: 0; }
      main { margin: 0 auto; max-width: 760px; padding: 76px 28px 110px; }
      a { color: #146c43; text-underline-offset: 3px; } code, pre { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
      .brand { align-items: center; color: #202124; display: flex; font-size: 1.06rem; font-weight: 750; gap: 9px; letter-spacing: -.02em; text-decoration: none; }.mark { background: #202124; border-radius: 5px; color: #fff; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: .75rem; padding: 4px 6px; }
      .eyebrow { color: #687076; font-size: .86rem; margin: 64px 0 15px; } h1 { font-size: clamp(2.65rem, 8vw, 4.4rem); letter-spacing: -.065em; line-height: .98; margin: 0; max-width: 650px; } .intro { color: #5b6166; font-size: 1.16rem; line-height: 1.65; margin: 25px 0 0; max-width: 620px; }
      .links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 18px; margin: 28px 0 58px; }.links a { font-size: .93rem; font-weight: 650; }.links a:first-child { background: #202124; border-radius: 6px; color: #fff; padding: 10px 14px; text-decoration: none; }
      section { border-top: 1px solid #dedfdf; padding: 42px 0; } h2 { font-size: 1.38rem; letter-spacing: -.03em; margin: 0 0 14px; } h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin: 0 0 5px; } p { color: #555b60; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 16px; } ul { color: #555b60; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; }
      pre { background: #f3f4f3; border: 1px solid #e2e4e2; border-radius: 7px; color: #303437; font-size: .84rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 20px 0 0; overflow: auto; padding: 18px; } .muted { color: #747b80; font-size: .88rem; margin-top: 14px; }
      .steps { display: grid; gap: 23px; margin-top: 24px; }.step { display: grid; gap: 14px; grid-template-columns: 27px 1fr; }.number { color: #146c43; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: .84rem; font-weight: 700; padding-top: 2px; }.step p { font-size: .94rem; margin: 0; }
      .note { background: #f5faf6; border-left: 3px solid #4ba66e; color: #395443; font-size: .92rem; line-height: 1.55; margin-top: 25px; padding: 13px 15px; }.footer { color: #858b90; font-size: .82rem; padding-top: 30px; }
      @media (max-width: 560px) { main { padding: 42px 21px 75px; }.eyebrow { margin-top: 50px; } }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <a class="brand" href="#top"><span class="mark">$</span> etg</a>
      <div id="top" class="eyebrow">env to GitHub</div>
      <h1>GitHub environment secrets, without the busywork.</h1>
      <p class="intro">etg turns a local <code>env.&lt;environment&gt;.to.github</code> file into GitHub environment secrets. Review the change, then sync it with one command.</p>
      <div class="links"><a href="#install">Install with Homebrew</a><a href="#usage">See how it works ↓</a></div>

      <section>
        <h2>Small, deliberate, and safe by default.</h2>
        <ul><li>One local file for each environment: production, staging, preview, and more.</li><li><code>--dry-run</code> previews key names and value lengths—never secret values.</li><li>Built on the GitHub CLI you already use, so authentication stays simple.</li></ul>
      </section>

      <section id="usage">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>Create a local file for the environment you want to update.</p>
        <pre>{example}</pre>
        <div class="steps"><div class="step"><span class="number">01</span><div><h3>Preview first</h3><p>Run <code>etg --dry-run</code> to see exactly which keys are ready to sync. Nothing is sent to GitHub.</p></div></div><div class="step"><span class="number">02</span><div><h3>Sync when ready</h3><p>Run <code>etg</code>. Existing secrets are updated and missing ones are created in the matching <code>production</code> environment.</p></div></div><div class="step"><span class="number">03</span><div><h3>Inspect remotely</h3><p>Use <code>etg info</code> for available environments and <code>etg list production</code> for secret names.</p></div></div></div>
      </section>

      <section id="install">
        <h2>Install</h2>
        <p>Install etg with Homebrew, then connect the GitHub CLI to the account and repository you want to manage.</p>
        <pre>{install}</pre>
        <pre>{run}</pre>
        <p class="muted">Requires the <a href="https://cli.github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub CLI</a>. etg uses your active <code>gh</code> session—there is no separate account to configure.</p>
        <div class="note">Keep real values local. <code>env.*.to.github</code> files are ignored by Git; commit a safe <code>.example</code> file instead.</div>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">etg · env to GitHub · <a href="https://github.com/mattrbdr/envtogithub">View the project on GitHub</a></footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
